<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><a href="/keine-kosten-zu-hoch">keine Kosten zu hoch</a> is another contest entry, this time for the Reimagining Contest.</p>
<p>I honestly have zero idea where the idea came from. I <em>will</em> say that, canonically, Entity KOLOSS is meant to be the Biblical Behemoth, and that at least some motivation for the project was our lack of a canonical Behemoth on the site, despite the presence of a veritable <a href="/scp-169">Leviathan</a>. I'll also say that WWII supertech is an underexplored trope in site fiction. I've created a headcanon for Otto Weber, which has been elaborated on in other works and will be further elaborated on later in this author page and in later works. I don't have much else to say besides that this is also what I will call an Elseworld MacCanon story.</p>
